  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Traffic Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles & responsibilities:</strong></p><p>1. Coordination with Traffic consultant as well as Construction team/Civil Design Consultant/etc. for Traffic Diversion and Final Road reinstatement plan Development including any traffic related activities (TIA, etc.)</p><p>2. Carryout Traffic Diversion approval process and coordination with LTA including PSR and safety submission</p><p>3. Carryout Traffic Diversion related coordination with Authorities/Stakeholders</p><p>4. Carryout Traffic Diversion Related Civil work design. (Drain Diversion, Retaining Wall) with coordination with Design Consultant, PE, etc.</p><p><strong>Requirements and relevant experience are as below:</strong></p><p>1. Bachelor’s / Master’s Degree of Transportation Engineering or close discipline;</p><p>2. Minimum 3 years of experience in Traffic related work</p><p>3. Minimum 2 years of experience with LTA Project</p><p>4. Be well-aware of Traffic diversion plan approval process in LTA Project</p><p>5. Be well-aware of Traffic related coordination process with authorities/stakeholders</p><p>6. Be well-aware of Underground Structure/Traffic Decking System/Construction Sequences.</p><p>* Candidates who are willing to commit their involvement in the assigned project until the successful completion of project would be an advantage.</p><p>* Interested applicants are required to submit their detailed CV and state their current and expected salary.</p>",
